Security agents should work together for the well-being of Kenyans, Gatundu North MP Kigo Njenga (pictured) has said.Interaction between the police, administrators and residents improves security, he said. Njenga called for unity and proper communication among security officers and the public.He spoke in Juja on Friday during a farewell party for outgoing deputy county commissioner Daniel Nyameti. He said Nyameti has left the area better that he found it.